menu "DALI Component Configuration"

    comment "Part 101 (Physical Layer / RMT Driver) is always enabled."

    config DALI_PART102_ENABLED
        bool "Enable Part 102 — Control Gear (luminaires, drivers)"
        default y
        help
            Include support for IEC 62386-102 control gear: DAPC dimming,
            scene/group commands, commissioning (binary-search address
            assignment), and Part 209 DT8 colour control.

            Disable this option if your application only uses Part 103
            input devices and does not control any luminaires or drivers.

    config DALI_PART209_ENABLED
        bool "Enable Part 209 — DT8 Colour Control (CCT / RGB / RGBWAF)"
        default y
        depends on DALI_PART102_ENABLED
        help
            Include IEC 62386-209 (DT8) colour and colour-temperature
            control helpers (dali_master_set_colour / dali_enable_device_type).

            Requires Part 102 to be enabled. Disable this option if your
            luminaires are single-channel (DT6 or similar) and do not
            support colour control.

    config DALI_PART103_ENABLED
        bool "Enable Part 103 — Input Devices (sensors, push-buttons)"
        default y
        help
            Include support for IEC 62386-103 input devices: commissioning,
            device-level queries, and instance-level commands.

            Disable this option if your application only controls luminaires
            and does not use any DALI input devices.

    config DALI_PART303_304_ENABLED
        bool "Enable Part 303/304 — Occupancy & Light Sensor helpers"
        default y
        depends on DALI_PART103_ENABLED
        help
            Include IEC 62386-303 (occupancy sensor) and IEC 62386-304
            (light sensor) convenience wrappers.

            Requires Part 103 to be enabled. Disable this option if you
            use Part 103 input devices but do not need the occupancy/light
            sensor helper functions.

endmenu
